name: BBCWorld
text:
Not enough votes have been counted for Trump or Biden to claim victory
Because of the time it takes to count the huge number of postal votes cast during this pandemic election, it could take days
And if there are legal challenges, it might even take weeks
https://t.co/Ej7mVOwpG7 https://t.co/WTex1W1Cp8

name: BBCWorld
text:
A few key battleground states decide the election

So far the race is still very close in those crucial competitive states

In some of those tight races, officials haven't even started counting postal votes, and those could change everything

 https://t.co/Ej7mVOwpG7 https://t.co/II9dcUb4Jd

name: BBCWorld
text:
Key states include:

Florida: Projected for Trump

Arizona: The state has not voted Democrat since 1996 but looks like a potential gain for Biden

Wisconsin and Pennsylvania: These states haven't started counting postal votes which could take days

 https://t.co/Ej7mVOwpG7 https://t.co/gMv5hRiWeM

name: BBCWorld
text:
Both candidates have addressed their supporters

Joe Biden urged patience saying: "We're going to win this" 

Donald Trump then tweeted: "We are up BIG, but they are trying to steal the election." Twitter has flagged that tweet as potentially misleading

https://t.co/Ej7mVOwpG7 https://t.co/5lztqJQadb

name: BBCWorld
text:
Senate elections are also happening:

- Trump ally Senator Graham is projected to win in S. Carolina
- Marjorie Taylor Greene (Rep), supporter of the QAnon conspiracy theory won her seat 
- Democrats lost Alabama, but gained Colorado from the Republicans
https://t.co/Ej7mVOwpG7 https://t.co/uuEIlLS3gZ

name: BBCWorld
text:
We might not know the result for days as decisive postal votes are counted

Trump has said previously that he would mount legal challenges if the result is close which could potentially take weeks

The only thing we can do is wait and see

https://t.co/Ej7mVOwpG7 https://t.co/NPw9O6vLJk
